      <!-- APPLICATION CATEGORIES -->
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(290px,1fr));gap:18px;margin-bottom:60px;">

        <!-- 1. National Security & Border -->
        <div style="background:linear-gradient(180deg,#1a0e0e,#0a0608);border:1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.30);border-radius:14px;padding:24px;">
          <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#fca5a5;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 10px;font-weight:700;">01 · National Security</p>
          <h3 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 14px;letter-spacing:-0.01em;color:#fee2e2;">Border surveillance, stealth-class</h3>
          <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;font-size:13px;line-height:1.55;color:#cfd6da;">
            <li><b style="color:#fca5a5;">Stealth perch &amp; persistent watch.</b> Bees alight on canopy / rock / fenceline for hours, drawing &lt;1 mW idle. AESA wing detects motion + heat signatures and only un-perches on a confirmed cue. Zero acoustic profile, low radar cross-section, multi-spectral skin (visual + IR + RAM).</li>
            <li><b style="color:#fca5a5;">Swarm cordon at LoC / LAC.</b> 5,000 bees blanket a 40 km corridor. Each carries a 3 cm baseline so the swarm acts as a sparse synthetic-aperture radar — sub-metre resolution at standoff. Infiltrators tracked through tree cover.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#fca5a5;">AGI-grade target discrimination.</b> Onboard reasoner separates a goat from a soldier, a tourist from a hostile, civilian crossing from organised infiltration. Edge inference is sub-watt; only the verdict goes upstream.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#fca5a5;">Mother SSTO as theatre relay.</b> Loiters at 18 km, holds the swarm command + comms, feeds GHQ a continuous picture. Reposition continent-wide in under an hour.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- 2. Public Safety & Crowd -->
        <div style="background:linear-gradient(180deg,#161020,#070310);border:1px solid rgba(168,85,247,0.30);border-radius:14px;padding:24px;">
          <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#d8b4fe;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 10px;font-weight:700;">02 · Public Safety</p>
          <h3 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 14px;letter-spacing:-0.01em;color:#ede9fe;">Cities, rallies, melas, riots</h3>
          <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;font-size:13px;line-height:1.55;color:#cfd6da;">
            <li><b style="color:#d8b4fe;">Crowd density &amp; stampede prediction.</b> Bees fly a 30 m grid over a Kumbh / public rally. Compute density per m², flag pressure waves before a stampede forms. Local control gets a 2-minute lead.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#d8b4fe;">Lost-child / missing-person locate.</b> The whole swarm runs a face / dress signature in parallel across the venue. Latency from query to find: under 90 seconds.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#d8b4fe;">Counter-terror perimeter.</b> Persistent 360° watch on stadium / convention / temple complex. Bees identify abandoned bags, unattended vehicles, unauthorised drones, and route the alert to the nearest officer's earpiece.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#d8b4fe;">Riot de-escalation.</b> Read crowd temperature in real time. Direct officers to friction points before they ignite. All footage is auditable — citizens' privacy claims are testable against logs.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- 3. Infrastructure & Civic -->
        <div style="background:linear-gradient(180deg,#0e1a17,#020a07);border:1px solid rgba(74,222,128,0.30);border-radius:14px;padding:24px;">
          <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#86efac;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 10px;font-weight:700;">03 · Civic Infrastructure</p>
          <h3 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 14px;letter-spacing:-0.01em;color:#dcfce7;">Roads, grids, sanitation, water</h3>
          <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;font-size:13px;line-height:1.55;color:#cfd6da;">
            <li><b style="color:#86efac;">Highway &amp; road health.</b> Bees photograph every kilometre at sub-millimetre resolution. Potholes, cracks, missing signage, blocked storm drains — auto-routed to the responsible PWD division with GPS + severity score. National Highway Authority gets a live map.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#86efac;">Power grid &amp; tower inspection.</b> Thermal + visual on every transmission tower, transformer, and insulator. Catches hotspots before flashover, vegetation encroachment before a fire, rust on a steel lattice before failure.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#86efac;">Water bodies &amp; sewage.</b> Surface scan of lakes / rivers / drains. Detect algal bloom, sewage discharge, illegal dumping, encroachment on water bodies. Reports route to municipal commissioners + Pollution Control Board with timestamped evidence.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#86efac;">Swachata Bharat — measured, not slogan.</b> Per-ward cleanliness index sampled hourly. Litter accumulation rate, garbage truck schedule adherence, public-toilet condition, open defecation hotspots. Municipal corporations get an objective scorecard — and so do citizens.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#86efac;">Heritage &amp; monument condition.</b> Periodic scans of stupas, temples, forts. Structural cracks tracked over years. ASI gets early warning before a wall comes down.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- 4. Disaster Response -->
        <div style="background:linear-gradient(180deg,#1a1207,#0a0703);border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.30);border-radius:14px;padding:24px;">
          <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#fde68a;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 10px;font-weight:700;">04 · Disaster Response</p>
          <h3 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 14px;letter-spacing:-0.01em;color:#fef3c7;">Floods, fires, earthquakes, cyclones</h3>
          <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;font-size:13px;line-height:1.55;color:#cfd6da;">
            <li><b style="color:#fde68a;">Search &amp; rescue, post-collapse.</b> Bees enter rubble through gaps no human can. Find survivors by heat + sound, mark coordinates for NDRF teams.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#fde68a;">Forest-fire perimeter map.</b> Live edge tracking + hotspot prediction. State Forest Departments get a fire-line map updated every 30 seconds.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#fde68a;">Flood damage assessment.</b> First 6-hour map of inundated villages, breached bunds, broken bridges. Insurance + relief disbursement starts from satellite-grade ground truth — not estimates.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#fde68a;">Mountain-rescue support.</b> Stealth class operates above 5,000 m. Avalanche victim search, lost-trekker locate, route confirmation for ITBP / Air Force.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- 5. Internet Prediction & Spectrum -->
        <div style="background:linear-gradient(180deg,#0a1820,#02080d);border:1px solid rgba(34,211,238,0.30);border-radius:14px;padding:24px;">
          <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#67e8f9;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 10px;font-weight:700;">05 · Connectivity Forecast</p>
          <h3 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 14px;letter-spacing:-0.01em;color:#cffafe;">Internet prediction &amp; spectrum mapping</h3>
          <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;font-size:13px;line-height:1.55;color:#cfd6da;">
            <li><b style="color:#67e8f9;">Coverage truth map.</b> Bees fly the actual streets of a city / village / valley and measure 4G/5G/satellite signal at house-level resolution. Operators can no longer claim coverage they don't deliver.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#67e8f9;">Internet weather forecast.</b> Predict per-cell congestion 30 minutes ahead from rush hours + events + weather. Operators reroute traffic before users see buffering.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#67e8f9;">Spectrum interference detection.</b> Identify unauthorised emitters, jamming, spoofing in real time. TRAI gets evidence; intel agencies get a tactical lead.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#67e8f9;">Last-mile deployment planning.</b> Before fibre is dug, the swarm gives an exact terrain + line-of-sight map. ISP saves months of survey time.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- 6. Agriculture & Environment -->
        <div style="background:linear-gradient(180deg,#0c1605,#040801);border:1px solid rgba(132,204,22,0.30);border-radius:14px;padding:24px;">
          <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#bef264;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 10px;font-weight:700;">06 · Agriculture &amp; Climate</p>
          <h3 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 14px;letter-spacing:-0.01em;color:#ecfccb;">Farms, forests, air, ice</h3>
          <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;font-size:13px;line-height:1.55;color:#cfd6da;">
            <li><b style="color:#bef264;">Per-plant agronomy.</b> Multi-spectral imaging of every plant in a field. Disease, water stress, nitrogen need — detected before the human eye sees it. State Krishi departments get actionable intelligence.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#bef264;">Forest cover &amp; encroachment.</b> Continuous monitoring of reserved forest boundaries. Illegal felling, encroachment, mining — all flagged with photographic evidence.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#bef264;">Air quality at street resolution.</b> PM2.5, NOx, ozone — mapped per neighbourhood, not per city. CPCB + city governments get policy-grade truth.</li>
            <li><b style="color:#bef264;">Glacier &amp; coastline tracking.</b> The Grandmother provides continental-scale climate observation. Glacier retreat, coastal erosion, sea-level rise — measured against a stable orbital reference.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Why the swarm makes this possible -->
      <div style="background:linear-gradient(180deg,#0a1c25,#06141d);border:1px solid rgba(120,200,220,0.16);border-radius:14px;padding:28px;margin-bottom:60px;">
